text: Kajaani () is a town in the region of Kainuu, Finland. In 2009, it had a population of about 38,000. It covers an area of . The forestry and lumber industries are important in Kajaani.Factum, part 3, page 204, Finnish 003 1 398 The former municipality of Vuolijoki was merged with Kajaani in 2007. ==References== == Other websites == * The official Kajaani page Category:Towns in Finland Category:Municipalities of Kainuu
